  "body": "This fixes a problem where, if one is using the default, then on\r\nstartup, the check_data_dir sanity check fails, printing a warning to\r\nthe console that would be easy to ignore.\r\n\r\nI gather this doesn't cause problems elsewhere because other code is\r\ncalling `join` to create subpaths.\r\n\r\nIt seems to me that having an empty default is error-prone (as here), so the fix should be to not willingly set it to \"\" (additional startup checks that no paths are \"\" would be even better).\r\n\r\nI put a special case into the validation code to account for the change from \"\" to \"./\" on upgrade. I have tested it manually.\r\n\r\n## What have you changed? (mandatory)\r\n\r\nSet `DEFAULT_DATA_DIR` to \"./\".\r\n\r\n## What are the type of the changes? (mandatory)\r\n\r\n- Bug fix (change which fixes an issue)\r\n\r\n## How has this PR been tested? (mandatory)\r\n\r\nManually.\r\n\r\n## Refer to a related PR or issue link (optional)\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/tikv/tikv/issues/4392",
